&lt;em&gt;One very popular approach is Qigong. Qi, the natural energu that’s supposed to flow through us and around us, could be conflated with the energy terms in Kabbalah(e.g. shefah and nitzotzot).&lt;/em&gt;
So when is it no longer Kabbalah? Is there a point when it is illegitimate to still call it kabbalah? Is there a point when we should just call it Qi and leave out any connection to Judiasm? Can everything be called kabbalah?
